The '''Manarai Mountains''' were twin mountain peaks, located in one of the few places on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] that remained free of skyscrapers and cities. They were located near [[Orowood]] and the famous [[Imperial Palace/Legends|Imperial Palace]], and were east of the [[Great Western Sea/Legends|Western Sea]]. Many floating restaurants revolved around the Mountains, giving patrons a unique view of the natural wonders.

The Manarai Mountains included: the tallest peak, [[Umate/Legends|Umate]]; the restaurant [[Manarai]]; the [[Monument Plaza/Legends|Monument Plaza]]; and the home of the [[Flames of Umate]] cult. ''[[Lusankya/Legends|Lusankya]]'' was hidden beneath the Manarai. [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] built a private retreat on the mountains shortly after establishing his [[Jedi academy]].

During the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Battle of Coruscant (Yuuzhan Vong War)|assault on Coruscant]], the Manarai Mountains were destroyed along with Luke's private retreat.

The mountains might have had native plant life.

{{Nature-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The Manarai Mountains were created by [[Timothy Zahn]] for ''[[Heir to the Empire]]''. He stated that he knew that Coruscant was a [[Planet/Legends|planet]]-wide city, but assumed that there would still be a few areas of wilderness, as this would appeal to rich and powerful types who would want to build private country retreats.<ref name="Heir 20">''[[Heir to the Empire: The 20th Anniversary Edition]]''</ref>

